{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17638999","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17638999"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:02:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:02:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17755"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17755","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17755"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.78,0.19,0.04,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10469"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72385"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10469","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10469"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17755"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57855"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10019"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24438"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24440"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24523"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72385","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72385"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EJaundice can be classified in a number of different ways and a standard approach is:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Epre-hepatic\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ehepatic\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Epost-hepatic\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a post-hepatic cause of jaundice?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Cholangiocarcinoma","Gilbert syndrome","Haemolytic anaemia","Non-alcoholic fatty liver disease","Viral hepatitis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EPre-hepatic and hepatic causes tend to be called medical jaundice, whereas post-hepatic or obstructive causes are generally referred to as surgical jaundice.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECholangiocarcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a cancer of the bile ducts that can cause obstruction of bile flow, leading to post-hepatic jaundice. This type of jaundice is characterised by conjugated hyperbilirubinaemia and is often associated with symptoms such as dark urine and pale stools, as seen in this patient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EViral hepatitis\u003C/strong\u003E causes hepatocellular damage, leading to intra-hepatic jaundice, not post-hepatic. It typically presents with elevated liver enzymes and mixed hyperbilirubinaemia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGilbert syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is a benign condition causing mild unconjugated hyperbilirubinaemia due to reduced activity of the enzyme glucuronyltransferase. It does not cause post-hepatic jaundice.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHaemolytic anaemia\u003C/strong\u003E leads to pre-hepatic jaundice due to increased breakdown of red blood cells, resulting in elevated levels of unconjugated bilirubin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-alcoholic fatty liver disease\u003C/strong\u003E is a cause of intra-hepatic jaundice due to liver cell damage and does not typically cause post-hepatic jaundice.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Post-hepatic jaundice is caused by obstruction of bile flow after it leaves the liver.","Cholangiocarcinoma is a common cause of post-hepatic jaundice due to bile duct obstruction.","Viral hepatitis and Gilbert syndrome are not causes of post-hepatic jaundice."],"references":["Joseph A, Samant H. Jaundice. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK544252/","Tajiri T, Yoshida H, Mamada Y, Taniai N, Yokomuro S, Mizuguchi Y. Diagnosis and initial management of cholangiocarcinoma with obstructive jaundice. World J Gastroenterol. 2008 May 21;14(19):3000-5. doi: 10.3748/wjg.14.3000. PMID: 18494050; PMCID: PMC2712166.","Lleo A, Colapietro F, Maisonneuve P, Aloise M, Craviotto V, Ceriani R, Rimassa L, Badalamenti S, Donadon M, Pedicini V, Repici A, Di Tommaso L, Voza A, Torzilli G, Aghemo A. Risk Stratification of Cholangiocarcinoma Patients Presenting with Jaundice: A Retrospective Analysis from a Tertiary Referral Center. Cancers (Basel). 2021 Apr 25;13(9):2070. doi: 10.3390/cancers13092070. PMID: 33922972; PMCID: PMC8123266."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57855"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17755"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57855","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57855"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-21T10:53:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-21T10:54:25+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10469"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72385"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":n